Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer and the Los Angeles Dodgers scored three more runs in the seventh to beat the San Diego Padres 7-2 on Thursday night and clinch their 11th NL West title in 12 years
Post-Match Reflections: The Los Angeles Dodgers clinched their 11th NL West title in 12 years
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers scored 5 runs in the 7th inning
The game was played at Dodger Stadium in front of 52,433 fans
